        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-grid">
        <div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <div class="faq-q">Do I need a referral?</div>
            <div class="faq-a">
              Many patients are referred by their primary care doctor, surgeon,
              or specialist, but self-referrals are welcome depending on your
              insurance plan. Call our office and we‚Äôll help you understand
              what‚Äôs required.
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <div class="faq-q">What should I bring to my first visit?</div>
            <div class="faq-a">
              Please bring a photo ID, insurance card, a list of medications and
              allergies, and any recent wound-related records or imaging if you
              have them. If you have special dressings currently in use, bring
              those as well.
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <div class="faq-q">How long does wound healing usually take?</div>
            <div class="faq-a">
              Healing time depends on the type of wound, circulation, infection,
              blood sugar control, and other medical conditions. At your visit,
              we‚Äôll review your specific situation and outline expectations for
              your healing plan.
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <div class="faq-q">How often will I need to be seen?</div>
            <div class="faq-a">
              Most patients are seen weekly or every other week at the
              beginning, then less frequently as the wound improves. Your
              schedule is customized to your needs and response to treatment.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-note">
          <strong>Important:</strong> If you have sudden severe pain, fever,
          spreading redness, foul odor, or concern for emergency infection,
          please seek immediate care in an emergency department or call 911.
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

